pdf_summary: DOWSIL™ 790 Silicone Building Sealant is a one-part, ultra-low-modulus, neutral-curing silicone sealant designed for high-movement weathersealing applications [25]. It exhibits excellent unprimed adhesion to masonry and most porous substrates, and conforms to ISO 11600F-25LM [25]. The sealant maintains its properties in extreme weather conditions and is easy to apply across a wide temperature range [25].
justification: This data sheet confirms that DOWSIL™ 790 is a single-component, neutral-curing silicone joint sealant [18]. It also states that it's non-staining and has plus 100 percent and minus 50 percent movement capability and adheres to ASTM C 920, Type S, Grade NS, Class 100/50, Use NT [6, 18].

pdf_summary: GE SCS2700 SilPruf™ LM silicone weatherproofing sealant is a one-component, low-modulus, neutral-cure silicone sealant used for new or remedial weatherproofing applications [14]. It provides primerless adhesion to many substrates and finishes, is low in VOCs, and offers thermal stability [14]. The cured silicone rubber exhibits long-term resistance to natural weathering, including extreme temperatures and UV radiation [14].
justification: This document describes GE SCS2700 SilPruf™ LM, a single-component, neutral-cure silicone sealant with +100/-50% movement capability [14]. It is designed for weatherproofing and offers primerless adhesion to various substrates [14]. This aligns with the specifications of GE Construction Sealants; SCS2700 Silpruf LM.

pdf_summary: Pecora 890NST is a one-part, neutral-curing, ultra-low modulus silicone sealant that will not stain natural stone [12]. It reacts with atmospheric moisture to form a durable, flexible building sealant [12]. This sealant is suitable for sealing expansion and control joints, perimeter sealing of doors and windows and adheres tenaciously to concrete, natural stones, masonry, steel, fluoropolymer painted and powder coated aluminum, wood, vinyl and many other plastics, generally without need for a primer, and performs equally well in new or remedial construction [12].
justification: This document confirms that Pecora 890NST is a non-staining, single-component, neutral-curing silicone sealant [11, 12]. It is an ultra-low modulus sealant designed for sealing expansion and control joints [11, 12]. It is designed primarily for sealing expansion and control joints in precast concrete panels, architectural and natural stone, metal curtainwalls, perimeter sealing of doors and windows [12].

pdf_summary: Sikasil® WS-290 FPS is a field pigmentable, low to no bleed, low modulus, one–component plus color pack, non-sag, elastomeric, neutral cure silicone sealant [15]. Sikasil® WS-290 FPS performs exceptionally well under dynamic conditions due to its ultra-low modulus, high extension/compression, recovery properties and strong adhesion to most building materials [15]. Sikasil® WS-290 FPS accommodates long-term movement of +100/-50 % in properly designed joints and is particularly well suited for use in Exterior Insulation Finish Systems (EIFS) [15].
justification: This document describes Sikasil® WS-290, a one-part, neutral-curing silicone sealant, which meets the requirements of ASTM C-920, Type S, Grade NS, Class 100/50, Use NT, M, G, A, O [1, 7, 15]. It also has +100/-50 % joint movement and is non-staining to most porous substrates [1, 7, 15]. It is designed for sealing expansion and control joints in precast concrete panels and metal curtain walls [7, 15].

pdf_summary: Spectrem 1 is a high-performance, single-component, moisture-cure, ultra-low modulus silicone sealant designed for dynamically moving joints [5, 9, 28]. It offers excellent adhesion to various substrates and is suitable for use in aluminum curtain walls, precast concrete panels, metal panels, and window perimeters [5, 9, 28]. The sealant provides resistance to driving rain, ozone, UV light, and temperature extremes, ensuring exceptional weatherability [5, 9, 28].
justification: This document confirms that Spectrem 1 is a single-component, non-sag, non-staining silicone joint sealant [2, 5, 9]. It complies with ASTM C 920, Type S, Grade NS, Class 100/50, Use NT; SWRI validated [2, 5, 9, 28]. It has an ultra-low modulus with +100/-50% movement accommodation and is suitable for dynamically moving joints [5, 9, 28].
